    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 24, 2026, centers on a high-ceiling core led by **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker**. **Gunnar Henderson** draws the day\u2019s premier matchup with an elite efficiency score of 83.29, benefiting from a 16% park adjustment and a favorable 14% platoon edge against Brayan Bello; however, managers must monitor the 34% rain risk, which threatens his otherwise ideal leadoff role. **Kyle Tucker** (73.60) remains a cornerstone start against Jameson Taillon, anchored by strong peripheral metrics and a 10% SP skill advantage. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (69.24) also presents a high-floor opportunity at 1B, as his 0.384 xwOBA suggests he is primed to capitalize on a favorable matchup against Gavin Williams despite a slight negative platoon adjustment.\n\nSeveral secondary plays are elevated by specific situational advantages. **Drake Baldwin** (64.49) and **Nasim Nunez** (62.48) represent savvy starts; **Drake Baldwin** benefits significantly from a soft matchup against Andrew Painter, while **Nasim Nunez** gains leverage from the 19% SP skill indicator, providing a rare high-efficiency boost for a lower-order hitter. Conversely, **Luis Robert Jr.** (49.86) is relegated to the fringes of the start threshold due to a poor park factor and a restrictive platoon disadvantage against Michael Lorenzen. **Heliot Ramos** (59.77) warrants attention as a \"starts only\" option; his score is buoyed by the wind and the presence of a slower-working pitcher, which historically elevates his potential for a stolen base, a category where we remain hyper-aggressive.\n\nThe most difficult benching decision involved **Nolan Schanuel**, whose 56.02 score fell narrowly behind the active roster\u2019s utility and outfield depth. While **Nolan Schanuel** provided solid efficiency, the optimizer prioritized the higher platoon-adjusted ceilings of **Andy Pages** and **Josh Jung**. Similarly, **Coby Mayo** (54.82) and **Brady House** (53.25) were bypassed; **Coby Mayo**\u2019s upside was capped by a projected bottom-of-the-order slot and the same weather risk shadowing **Gunnar Henderson**, while **Brady House** struggled to overcome the platoon penalty against Bryan Hudson. We will continue to monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all players to ensure these projections hold as the official cards are posted.",
